«Currently, we have four-month-old mice that used to be diabetic and are no longer so», he added.
The research is still in its initial stage, as indicated by Dr. Ehud Ur, a professor in the medical school at Dalhousie University in Halifax, Nova Scotia, and director of the clinical and scientific department of the Canadian Diabetes Association.
Like other specialists, he is skeptical about whether diabetes has a cure and emphasizes that these discoveries are not relevant for those who already suffer from type 1 diabetes.
