The 802.11n standard works on both 2.4Ghz and 5.0Ghz frequencies.
This will make it possible for your device to be compatible with previous versions of 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g; provided that the base station has dual radios.
The speeds of the 802.11n standard are much higher than those achieved by its predecessors, with a theoretical maximum throughput of 600 Mbps.
